text: Third day in a row @UPS that you said that a package was attempted to be delivered and it wasn't. I literally sat and watched out the window during the time it said it was attempted to be delivered. Way to lie to customers.

@GoonReviews Sorry for the miscommunication and can understand your frustration. Please DM my team your tracking details including tracking and phone number, name and full address on package. ^AT https://t.co/wKJHDXWGRQ
@UPSHelp Need someone to explain to me why you are able to be dishonest to customers.

@UPSHelp This had nothing to do with communication, but everything to do with being dishonest and lazy to your customers. A supervisor called me and said the package would be delivered Thurs (and Fri if I wasn't home) and it wasn't delivered either day.

@UPSHelp The package was time sensitive and I needed it by Friday, because Sat I had a convention doing product demo. So not only did I lose money leaving work early two days in a row to try and catch your driver, I lost money invested in the convention because I had no product to demo.

@UPSHelp Oh and to make things look immature, the driver had a different package to drop off yesterday and held the buzzer down until I answered the door, like I'm the jerk for calling his supervisor for not doing his job. I, for the life of me, cannot understand how you are in business.
